-- Altran Says 2010 Recovery Being Led by Auto-Industry Clients, Echos Says
-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 2010-10-06T04:43:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/altran-says-2010-recovery-being-led-by-auto-industry-clients-echos-says.html
French engineering company Altran
Technologies SA will have a better year in 2010 than it did in
2008, daily Les Echos reported, citing executive vice-president
Pascal Brier.  Since February and March, Altran has witnessed a recovery
in demand led by clients in the auto industry, the newspaper
cited Brier as saying.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Whitehouse at 
 dwhitehouse1@bloomberg.net  